 1996-00531996-01-230INDUSTRY,  ,  ,  , 
PrecisAppointment of ROY WHITNEY, of Calgary, Alberta, as a member of the National Aboriginal Economic Development Board and designation of ROY WHITNEY as Chairperson of that Board; appointment of ROGER AUGUSTINE, of Newcastle, New Brunswick; GARY BOSGOED, of Regina, Saskatchewan; GARDA MORAN, of Portage la Prairie, Manitoba; GRAHAM TUPLIN, of Lower Montague, Prince Edward Island; and MARY ELIZABETH JAMIESON, of Ohsweken, Ontario, as members of the National Aboriginal Economic Development for a term of two years; and appointment of STAN BEARDY, of Muskrat Dam, Ontario; SHIRLEY ANNE HARLEY, of Fort Good Hope, Northwest Territories; ROBERT LOUIE, of Kelowna, British Columbia; DWIGHT A. DOREY, of Truro, Nova Scotia; MARY MACDONALD, of Toronto, Ontario; of KEITH BELISLE, of White River, Ontario; J.C. ROGER WARREN, of Verdun, Quebec; CHESLEY ANDERSEN, of Nain, Labrador, Newfoundland; and CYNTHIA BERTOLIN, of Edmonton, Alberta, as members of the National Aboriginal Economic Development Board for a term of three years.
